    Scanner x = new Scanner (System.in);
    System.out.print(&quot;Enter the size: &quot;);
    int num = x.nextInt();

    int array [] = new int[num];
    BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));
    String lines = br.readLine();    
        
    String[] strs = lines.trim().split(&quot;\\s+&quot;);
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; strs.length; i++) {
        array[i] = Integer.parseInt(strs[i]);
    }

This will store the integers in the variable `array`.

Note: This works well, if you are sure that the `size` entered and then the no. of `values` entered are same. You might have to handle scenarios where they doesn&#39;t match.

